2 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
3 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
4 HOUSE BILL 4343 By: Moore of the House
5 and
6 Reinhardt of the Senate
7
8 AS INTRODUCED
9 An Act relating to property appraisers; amending 28
O.S. 2021, Section 49.1, which relates to appraiser
10 and commissioner compensation; providing compensation
amount; and providing an effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 28 O.S. 2021, Section 49.1, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 49.1. Any appraiser or commissioner appointed by the
17 district court in condemnation or escheat cases shall be paid Three
18 Hundred Fifty Dollars ($350.00) for services rendered and expense
19 expenses incurred an amount as determined by the district judge,
20 before whom such proceedings is pending.
21 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
22
23 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON JUDICIARY AND PUBLIC SAFETY
OVERSIGHT, dated 02/26/2026 - DO PASS.
